text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 2.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 3.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 2.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 3.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 2.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 3.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 4.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

 2.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 3.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 4.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 5.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

 1.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 2.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 3.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 4.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 5.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

text_1:

 1.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 2.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 3.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 4.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 5.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 4.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 5.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

 4.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 5.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 3.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 4.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 5.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 3.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 4.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 5.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany

This happened on the day December 3rd in history:

Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

 Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

 The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 2.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 3.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 4.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 1.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 2.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 3.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 4.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 5.The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
 6.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 4.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 5.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.

Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 1.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 2.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 3.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 4.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 5.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The Duquesne Country and Athletic Club defeats an all-star collection of early football players 16–0.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.

 Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 2.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 3.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 4.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 5.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 1.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 2.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 3.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 4.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 5.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
 4.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 5.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.

Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

 The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

 Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 2.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 3.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 4.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 5.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
